Local Third Sector Infrastructure Provision</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>ES/H03868X/1</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The Fellowship will address the following objectives:&lt;/p>

&lt;ol>
 

 &lt;li>To develop a framework and methodology to assist local and regional third sector infrastructure organisations to contribute to local and regional economic policy.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To review available secondary datasets and bespoke third sector surveys.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To make recommendations to local and regional partners as to research designs and questions to better inform policy making in the future.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To build university-third sector relationships and understanding.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>To build the capacity of the third sector to contribute to policy making.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>

&lt;p>The Fellowship will undertake the following tasks:&lt;/p>

&lt;ol>
 

 &lt;li>A review of local, regional and national third sector secondary data and surveys. This will primarily focus on: NSTSO and CLG Place Survey; IMD and CAA results; and the use of local survey evidence. &lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Discussions with regional public agencies. &lt;/li>

 &lt;li>The development of a methodology and framework for understanding the contribution of the third sector.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>The piloting of the methodology in four local authority areas. The following four case study areas will be used: East Riding; City of York; Sheffield City; and Wakefield District.&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Dissemination of the findings of the project at local, regional and national levels (see Impact Plan).&lt;br />&lt;/li>
